==English==

===Proverb===
'''[[curiosity]] [[killed]] [[the]] [[cat]]'''

# Knowing some things can be dangerous, so don't be so [[curious]] to know them.

====Translations====
*Portuguese: [[a curiosidade matou o gato]]
*Russian: [[от любопытства кошка сдохла]] (the cat died from its curiousity), [[любопытной Варваре на базаре нос оторвали]] (the nosy Barbara's nose was torn off at the market), [[много будешь знать - скоро состаришься]] (if you'll know much, you'll get old soon), [[меньше знаешь - крепче спишь]] (the les you know, the sounder you sleep)
*Español: [[La curiosidad mató al gato]]

